I loved this subtly spiced, aromatic and filling soup but the recipe is definitely under-spiced. I added an extra 2 tsp of cumin, another cinnamon stick and two pinched of cinnamon and it was perfect. Next time I'll definitely try the garam masala idea, but I was out of it when I made the soup. I'm usually an advocate wildly liberal seasoning of soups but in this case, I didn't want to overwhelm the saffron (after paying so much for it). I cooked the chickpeas first, then used the chickpea broth (plus 2 and 1/2 cubes of veg boullion) in place of the stock. I used sweet potatoes instead of squash. I also pureed about 1/4 of the veggies to thicken the soup. If you decide to cook chickpeas instead of using canned, I'd reccomend making hummus as a course after the soup. Also, as others mentioned, the soup thickens considerably the second day which is something to keep in mind if you're making it ahead of time.

