Rating: 4
This soup is outstanding. I am a lover of soups in the winter and this one is perfect for cold winter nights. I did substitute 1/2T Garam Masala for the cinnamon and cumin with great success. (Not to mention that it makes the whole house smell wonderful.) I also increased the garlic to 3 large cloves. I thought about pureeing before I added the garbanzos but then decided against it. I am glad I did because on the second day the butternut squash seemed to melt into the broth making a much thicker base. Serve it with some nice hot flat bread.

Rating: 4
I absolutely loved this recipe. My fried from Yemen made a dish that tasted just like this once and I've always wanted the recipe. It's incredible. I made cous cous, which I served in each individual bowl, then poured the soup over it. To make cous cous, the ratio is 1 c. cous cous to 1 1/2 c. water. Boil the water, then add the cous cous and stir. Reduce heat to simmer and cover. Cook for 5 minutes and fluff occasionally with a fork while cooking. The cous cous really absorbs the broth...I might try to make it with a little extra broth next time.

